<inglise> Article 4 (a) is replaced by the following: </inglise>
<eesti> Artikli 4 punkt a asendatakse j&auml;rgmisega: </eesti>
<inglise> '(a) which have been completely sown and harvested and on which normal cultivation work has been carried out; to be considered as having been harvested, areas must have undergone an operation: </inglise>
<eesti> "a) mis on tervikuna t&auml;is k&uuml;lvatud ja millelt on saak koristatud ning millel on tehtud tavap&auml;raseid p&otilde;lluharimist&ouml;id; et kasvualasid saaks lugeda koristatuks, peavad seal vajalikud t&ouml;&ouml;d olema: </eesti>
<inglise> - carried out after seed formation, </inglise>
<eesti> - tehtud p&auml;rast seemnete moodustumist, </eesti>
<inglise> - aimed at terminating the growing cycle of the plant, and - carried out with the aim of using the stalk, with or without seed. </inglise>
<eesti> - suunatud taime kasvuts&uuml;kli l&otilde;petamisele ja tehtud kas seemnetega v&otilde;i seemneteta varre v&auml;&auml;rtustamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> The use referred to in the third indent shall be considered as having been desired if the plant has been pulled up or if it has been cut by a cutter bar operating, in the case of flax and hemp, at a maximum height of 10 cm and 20 cm respectively from the ground. </inglise>
<eesti> Kolmandas taandes nimetatud v&auml;&auml;rtustamist loetakse soovitavaks, kui taim on kitkutud v&otilde;i niidetud niiduagregaadiga, mis lina ja kanepi puhul t&ouml;&ouml;tab maapinnast k&otilde;ige enam vastavalt 10 cm ja 20 cm k&otilde;rgusel. </eesti>
<inglise> As regards the requirement as to the height of the cutter bar: </inglise>
<eesti> Seoses niiduagregaadi k&otilde;rguse n&otilde;udega: </eesti>
<inglise> - areas must be kept in a state allowing it to be verified during the 20 days following the date of submission of the aid application or of a declaration that harvesting operations has commenced, </inglise>
<eesti> - tuleb kasvualad hoida seisukorras, mis v&otilde;imaldab kontrolli 20 p&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast toetusetaotluse v&otilde;i koristust&ouml;&ouml;de alguse deklaratsiooni esitamise kuup&auml;eva, </eesti>
<inglise> - Member States shall take the measures necessary to verify fulfilment of that condition and may take special harvest conditions into account. </inglise>
<eesti> - liikmesriigid v&otilde;tavad nimetatud tingimuse t&auml;itmise kontrolliks vajalikud meetmed ja v&otilde;ivad arvesse v&otilde;tta koristuse eritingimusi." </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the seventh day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub seitsmendal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
